        "timestamp": "2021-05-13 11:35:39.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n@Antony, Could you provide some source/links to confirm that tornado is better than flask ?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "351fb28033fe5b0c7384bdd60c200bc16dca7ee1",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 7475,
          "name": "Antony Saputra",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "antony.saputra@est.tech",
          "username": "antonys"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2021-05-13 12:20:14.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> @Antony, Could you provide some source/links to confirm that tornado is better than flask ?\n\nHi Tomasz, \nthe main reason we consider tornado is better than flask is because flask is synchronous on handling its request (could not find Flask documentation that highlights this but here's an article that discuss it https://crossbario.com/blog/Going-Asynchronous-from-Flask-to-Twisted-Klein/). Tornado was chosen specifically rather than other async server is because its one of the available server options for connexion framework (https://pypi.org/project/connexion/1.0.38/)",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
